  ],
  "remarks": "CDi.007 Arrested in Kinshasa in March 2005 for UPC/L involvement in human rights abuses violations. Transferred to the ICC on 17 March 2006. Convicted by the ICC in March 2012 and sentenced to 14 years in prison.  On 1 December 2014, ICC appeals judges upheld Lubanga’s conviction and sentence. Transferred to a prison facility in the DRC on 19 December 2015 to serve out his sentence of imprisonment. He was released on 15 March 2020 after having served his ICC sentence.; Listing: Listed by 1533 Committee on: 1 Nov. 2005 (amended on 13 Oct. 2016 and 2 Nov. 2020)",
